cly available, as is the reconstructed volume.", "citations": [{"title": "Fast imaging of millimeter-scale areas with beam deflection transmission electron microscopy", "paperId": "58443df22b2e215c2a4110719b804d99a0effa1e"}, {"title": "SyConn2: dense synaptic connectivity inference for volume electron microscopy", "paperId": "d6cec5d1abd983b03355b8cd8bf1542123de10b7"}, {"title": "Connectomics of the Octopus vulgaris vertical lobe provides insight into conserved and novel principles of a memory acquisition network", "paperId": "91d5f72f8daca248b7f6bb20f88500e48ce0be16"}, {"title": "Expected affine: A registration method for damaged section in serial sections electron microscopy", "paperId": "5ce819e3fed985e5ba2c695d9a31cd59441288c2"}, {"title": "Quantitative Census of Local Somatic Features in Mouse Visual Cortex", "paperId": "142298f5b11bf2c76536c93aa256835d69dca723"}, {"title": "MorphoFeatures: unsupervised exploration of cell types, tissues and organs in volume electron microscopy", "paperId": "9d65de0286d6a8c0a02922f401ff26afcc2b26a6"}, {"title": "Petascale pipeline for precise alignment of images from serial section electron microscopy", "paperId": "a641df4e738354237c2ba9cdb13c7dbca7d58171"}, {"title": "RealNeuralNetworks.jl: An Integrated Julia Package for Skeletonization, Morphological Analysis, and Synaptic Connectivity Analysis of Terabyte-Scale 3D Neural Segmentations", "paperId": "574fe91260f796820916c763948b7b684295fff0"}, {"title": "Reconstruction of neocortex: Organelles, compartments, cells, circuits, and activity", "paperId": "ccaa41be013f921fbd28a9d190689e9a149693a7"}, {"title": "A scalable and modular automated pipeline for stitching of large electron microscopy datasets", "paperId": "04bf1d96ccb70d065700678de21ca9bb5e156372"}, {"title": "Neural architectures in the light of comparative connectomics", "paperId": "073839c50960c7ef03515aee950605ddbfa83099"}, {"title": "A connectome is not enough - what is still needed to understand the brain of Drosop